citation.case_name: New York Mobile Homes Assn. v. Steckel

html:
369 U.S. 150

82 S.Ct. 685

7 L.Ed.2d 782

NEW YORK MOBILE HOMES ASS'N et al.
v.
thomas B. STECKEL et al.

No. 609.

Supreme Court of the United States

March 19, 1962

William L. Clay, for appellants.

Louis J. Lefkowitz, Atty. Gen. of New York, Paxton Blair, Sol. Gen., and Ruth Kessler Toch, Asst. Sol. Gen., for appellees.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

2

Mr. Justice WHITTAKER took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
